Aanay. . .

32:50.400 --> 32:53.198
I hear_the retrial's
gomg well.

32:53.230 --> 32:56.063
Yeah, well, I don't know.

32:56.100 --> 32:59.206
Our state's attorney
seems intent on retrying me,

32:59.240 --> 33:00.502
no matter how thin
the evidence.

33:00.540 --> 33:03.077
Well, at least you're home.

33:03.110 --> 33:04.577
At least I'm home.

33:06.450 --> 33:07.371
So, Alicia,

33:07.410 --> 33:09.412
we need to reconvene
this morning With Kalinda.

33:09.450 --> 33:11.247
Supposedly, she's got
something on Life State.

33:11.290 --> 33:12.484
Oh, what do you know.

33:12.520 --> 33:14.488
Kalinda works
at Stern Lockhart.

33:14.520 --> 33:16.010
Small world.

33:16.060 --> 33:17.152
That's right.

33:17.190 --> 33:19.681
She used to work for you.
Mm-hmm.

33:22.300 --> 33:23.551
So, I'll see you later.

33:23.600 --> 33:25.124
Yup.

33:25.170 --> 33:26.523
Don't be late.

33:31.240 --> 33:34.437
(door opens and closes)

33:34.480 --> 33:36.573
He's great.

33:36.610 --> 33:38.407
I don't_ remember him
being so nice.

33:38.450 --> 33:40.372
Yeah.

33:41.480 --> 33:43.675
Please tell me you
have something good.

33:45.690 --> 33:48.352
Well, I'm not sure what it is.

33:48.390 --> 33:51.826
And my method for obtaining it
is not exactly legitimate.

33:51.860 --> 33:54.829
Illegitimate as in
"I can't use it in court,"

33:54.860 --> 33:58.159
or... we can go to jail?

33:58.200 --> 34:00.122
I downloaded firmware

34:00.170 --> 34:02.434
and cloned Patti Nyholm's phone,

34:02.470 --> 34:04.358
in order to intercept
her text messages.

34:04.410 --> 34:06.799
(chuckles)
What?

34:06.840 --> 34:09.138
You wanted something.
I got you something.

34:11.250 --> 34:13.241
(sighs)

34:14.750 --> 34:16.217
Okay, let's hear it.

34:17.450 --> 34:20.180
Well, apart from an alarming
flirtation with a guy that mows

34:20.220 --> 34:22.256
the lawn,

34:22.290 --> 34:24.224
she's hiding Pamela.

34:24.260 --> 34:25.659
Pamela. Pamela who?

34:25.690 --> 34:28.557
My guess is Pamela Pomeroy,
that claims manager.

34:28.600 --> 34:30.158
I think she's
ready to flip.

34:30.200 --> 34:32.259
She was on the stand.
She didn't say a thing.

34:32.300 --> 34:33.562
Yeah.

34:33.600 --> 34:36.091
"They're on to Pam.
They turn Pam,

34:36.140 --> 34:38.165
we lose everything."
My guess is, Pomeroy

34:38.210 --> 34:40.804
went one too many times to bat
for Life State.

34:40.840 --> 34:42.330
She's ready to spill.

34:42.380 --> 34:44.701
You really cloned Nyholm's cell?

34:44.750 --> 34:46.308
Yeah.

34:48.350 --> 34:49.578
You do that again,
don't tell me.

34:49.620 --> 34:51.247
No problem.

34:51.290 --> 34:52.746
I should talk to her.
(knock at door)

34:52.790 --> 34:54.257
SECRETARY:
Mr. Gardner?
Yeah?

34:54.290 --> 34:56.212
Did Alicia get
her laptop last night?

34:56.260 --> 34:57.488
Alicia?

34:57.520 --> 34:59.488
After you left,
she came back looking

34:59.530 --> 35:00.758
for her laptop in your office.

35:00.790 --> 35:02.326
Just making sure
she got it.

35:02.360 --> 35:04.794
Yeah, yeah, she got it.

35:10.640 --> 35:14.576
Okay, let's go see Pamela.

35:14.610 --> 35:16.475
Yeah.

35:32.190 --> 35:35.489
*

35:46.910 --> 35:48.639
Hi.

35:48.680 --> 35:50.329
I'm sorry about this morning.

35:50.380 --> 35:52.348
You don't have to be sorry.

35:52.380 --> 35:53.642
Can I come in?

35:53.680 --> 35:55.375
Yeah.

36:04.660 --> 36:07.527
So, you're my boss.

36:07.560 --> 36:09.448
I know.

36:12.330 --> 36:13.627
I'm a junior associate.

36:13.670 --> 36:15.638
I know.

36:22.310 --> 36:24.278
You came into my office.

36:24.310 --> 36:27.905
Last night after you
left, you came back
to my office-- why?

36:27.950 --> 36:31.579
Will... help me out, please?

36:31.620 --> 36:33.941
I mean, we had...

36:33.990 --> 36:36.311
We had...

36:36.360 --> 36:39.488
whatever we had at Georgetown,
and I just...

36:39.530 --> 36:41.418
But you came back.

36:42.530 --> 36:44.293
I know.

36:44.330 --> 36:45.467
It was wrong.

36:47.300 --> 36:49.291
Because you're married?

36:54.540 --> 36:56.337
Okay, I have a suggestion.

36:56.380 --> 36:58.371
I like work.

36:58.410 --> 36:59.809
I like working here.

37:01.650 --> 37:03.743
I don't want
everywhere I go to be a mess.

37:03.780 --> 37:06.442
We're not going to talk
about this.

37:06.490 --> 37:08.412
We're not going
to say any more, okay?

37:09.790 --> 37:11.382
Good.

37:11.430 --> 37:12.852
We're going to go to dinner

37:12.890 --> 37:15.529
in one week's time,
and we'll talk then.

37:18.800 --> 37:21.291
Please don't end up hating me.

37:21.340 --> 37:23.763
I need this job.
I mean, I'm...

37:23.800 --> 37:25.506
H, I mean that...

37:25.540 --> 37:28.429
I'm sorry...
Alicia.

37:28.480 --> 37:30.869
It's fine.

37:33.980 --> 37:35.971
We have bad timing.

37:40.490 --> 37:41.787
(sighs)

37:41.820 --> 37:45.278
We've always had bad timing.

38:00.670 --> 38:02.570
KALINDA:
Excuse me, Ms. Pomeroy?

38:03.410 --> 38:05.401
Oh, you're, uh...
Yes.

38:05.450 --> 38:06.542
Do you have a moment,
Ms. Pomeroy?

38:06.580 --> 38:07.808
I-I don't think
we should be talking.

38:07.850 --> 38:08.874
We just need a minute.

38:08.920 --> 38:11.388
Why are they trying to hide you?

38:11.420 --> 38:14.014
I-I have no idea what you're
talking about.

38:14.050 --> 38:15.756
Uh, I have to go.
Please!

38:15.790 --> 38:17.519
The Willoughbys...

38:17.560 --> 38:19.755
their child is dying.

38:19.790 --> 38:22.054
I saw it in your eyes.
You want to help.

38:22.100 --> 38:23.397
Please help.

38:23.430 --> 38:24.988
You saw it in my eyes?

38:25.030 --> 38:26.463
Really?

38:26.500 --> 38:28.058
What powers of perception.

38:28.100 --> 38:30.830
What do you see in my eyes now?

38:30.870 --> 38:32.667
I'm going home now.

38:32.710 --> 38:36.032
But... Nyholm said she
was trying to hide Pam.

38:37.610 --> 38:39.942
You guys are really clueless.

38:39.980 --> 38:41.618
She's not trying to hide it.

38:41.650 --> 38:43.641
It's closed already.

38:46.450 --> 38:48.088
"It"?

38:48.120 --> 38:49.451
WILL:
It's an acronym.

38:49.490 --> 38:53.529
PAM-- policy
application management.

38:53.560 --> 38:55.027
It's an off-site group

38:55.060 --> 38:58.052
of Life State employees who look
for application mistakes,

38:58.100 --> 39:00.398
but only after expensive
claims were filed.

39:00.430 --> 39:02.569
It's organized
post-claims underwriting.

39:02.600 --> 39:04.067
Yup. It's illegal
in some states,

39:04.100 --> 39:05.499
and legislation in Illinois

39:05.540 --> 39:06.768
is on the horizon.
Which explains why

39:06.810 --> 39:08.437
they shut it
and tried to bury it.

39:08.480 --> 39:10.630
Yeah, but we got it
with an illegally-obtained text.

39:10.680 --> 39:12.898
It's fruit of the poisonous
tree. We can't use it.

39:12.950 --> 39:15.510
We can use it.

39:15.550 --> 39:17.871
We just can't use it in court.

39:26.160 --> 39:27.127
(knocking)

39:27.160 --> 39:29.128
Not a good time.

39:29.160 --> 39:30.627
Sure, it is.

39:30.660 --> 39:32.799
(mechanical humming)
Suit yourself.

39:37.540 --> 39:39.531
Is that...?
Yeah.

39:43.840 --> 39:46.149
This case is over, Will.

39:46.180 --> 39:48.512
No.

39:48.550 --> 39:51.587
Life State is going to quietly
reinstate Kate's coverage

39:51.620 --> 39:54.043
in time for the surgery
this afternoon...

39:54.090 --> 39:55.910
or your client's
going to be dealing

39:55.960 --> 39:58.656
with a hell of a lot more
than one upset family.

39:58.690 --> 40:00.885
Here I go trembling again.

40:00.930 --> 40:03.194
We know about PAM.

40:03.230 --> 40:04.663
(humming stops)

40:06.500 --> 40:09.765
And do you know who's
sitting outside your
office right now?

40:09.800 --> 40:12.507
Jonathan Dobbs, the
insurance commissioner.

40:12.540 --> 40:14.872
(sighs)

40:14.910 --> 40:16.605
(Bluetooth beeps)
Tammy?

40:16.640 --> 40:18.699
_ Is ther_e_a man
in the waiting room?

40:20.010 --> 40:22.149
Describe him.

40:29.690 --> 40:31.487
(Bluetooth beeps off)

40:31.530 --> 40:33.020
How'd you do that?

40:33.060 --> 40:35.654
He's waiting to hear about PAM.

40:35.700 --> 40:39.124
An entire department dedicated
to finding specious ways

40:39.170 --> 40:41.832
to rescind policies
when patients need them most.

40:43.240 --> 40:44.969
Do you remember
when you asked me

40:45.010 --> 40:47.934
_how bad I can make an
insurance company look?

40:47.970 --> 40:50.177
Really bad, Patti.

40:50.210 --> 40:52.144
Drop your license bad.

40:52.180 --> 40:54.512
You got this illegally.

40:54.550 --> 40:56.518
You must have,
or we'd be in court.

40:56.550 --> 40:59.018
You want to take it to a judge
and sort it out there,

40:59.050 --> 41:00.039
or just cover Kate?

41:04.530 --> 41:06.521
Thank you.

41:07.530 --> 41:10.226
I, um... Ifailed her.

41:10.260 --> 41:11.898
Just one puff
of a cigarette,

41:11.930 --> 41:13.591
and I saw it
all going wrong.

41:15.000 --> 41:17.059
You have kids?

41:17.100 --> 41:19.102
No.

41:20.170 --> 41:21.831
I think it changes everything.

41:21.880 --> 41:23.029
Doesn't it?

41:24.610 --> 41:26.248
It does.

41:35.060 --> 41:37.949
Is he...? I can't tell if
he's smiling. Is he smiling?

41:37.990 --> 41:40.026
WILL:
I don't know.

41:40.060 --> 41:41.652
Take off your mask.

41:51.340 --> 41:53.729
You realize if one whiff
of PAM surfaces,

41:53.770 --> 41:55.704
we can trace back to your firm?

41:55.740 --> 41:58.038
I know what a confidentiality
agreement is, Patti.

41:58.080 --> 42:00.105
And you can't use it
in the class action suit.

42:00.150 --> 42:01.617
We'll find another way.

42:01.650 --> 42:03.641
I doubt that.

42:05.120 --> 42:07.088
How'd you find it?
Find what?

42:07.120 --> 42:08.951
PAM.

42:08.990 --> 42:10.617
Who's Pam?

42:13.130 --> 42:15.758
You two make a cute couple.

42:28.310 --> 42:29.868
Hey.

42:29.910 --> 42:31.798
How'd it go?

42:31.850 --> 42:34.068
The insurance guys?
Jonathan showed up, right?

42:34.110 --> 42:36.044
Oh, right. Yeah, he did.

42:36.080 --> 42:37.069
It worked.

42:37.120 --> 42:39.315
Our client got the surgery,
and it went well.

42:39.350 --> 42:41.215
All right...

42:42.690 --> 42:44.954
How was your day?
Good.

42:44.990 --> 42:49.825
I spent more time
with Pastor Isaiah.

42:54.270 --> 42:55.965
He wants us to go to church.

43:00.010 --> 43:02.638
Well, that would
be interesting.

43:10.780 --> 43:12.782
It's getting late.

43:22.060 --> 43:23.197
Good night, Peter.

